Sentencas: Two alternative oxygen electrodes (anodes), La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) and La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-delta (lanthanum strontium manganite)/YSZ (yttria stabilized zirconia), were tested in 10SclCeSZ (scandia and ceria stabilized zirconia) based electrolysis cells and electrochemically evaluated.
Titulo: Performance and Characterization of (La, Sr)MnO3/YSZ and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Electrodes for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cells

Sentencas: In all the samples, the impedance response at OCV is characterized by a small arc at high frequencies around 10 kHz assigned to the Ni/YSZ polarization and a larger arc at low frequencies at about 200 Hz associated with the oxygen electrode.
Titulo: Performance and Characterization of (La, Sr)MnO3/YSZ and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Electrodes for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cells

Sentencas: Lower polarization resistances were found for the LSCF electrode.
Titulo: Performance and Characterization of (La, Sr)MnO3/YSZ and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Electrodes for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cells

Sentencas: Good performance in electrolysis mode was measured at an operating temperature of 800 degrees C and using 70% H2O at the Ni/YSZ cathode.
Titulo: Performance and Characterization of (La, Sr)MnO3/YSZ and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Electrodes for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cells

Sentencas: Area specific resistance (ASR) values of 0.93 and 0.79 Omega.cm(2) Were obtained for the LSM/YSZ and the LSCF samples respectively.
Titulo: Performance and Characterization of (La, Sr)MnO3/YSZ and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Electrodes for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cells

Sentencas: After operation, we have observed a similar to 10% increase in the ohmic resistance for the LSM/YSZ sample.
Titulo: Performance and Characterization of (La, Sr)MnO3/YSZ and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Electrodes for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cells

Sentencas: This degradation was studied by both X-ray diffraction and scanning electron microscopy.
Titulo: Performance and Characterization of (La, Sr)MnO3/YSZ and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Electrodes for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cells

Sentencas: LSM/YSZ and LSCF are suggested as good candidates for oxygen electrodes in high temperature electrolysis cells.
Titulo: Performance and Characterization of (La, Sr)MnO3/YSZ and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Electrodes for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cells

Sentencas: Finally, good electrochemical performance was also observed in reversible fuel cell mode.
Titulo: Performance and Characterization of (La, Sr)MnO3/YSZ and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 Electrodes for Solid Oxide Electrolysis Cells
